The gross energy content of Potato is 18.7MJ/kg on a dry matter basis, 87.2% dry matter as fed for North American Potato (Feedipedia - Maize 2017). At the harvest moisture content of 79.2% (), the energy content of Potato is 3.9MJ/kg product weight
Source(s): 
Heuzé V., Tran G., Lebas F. (2017) Maize grain. Feedipedia, a programme by INRAE, CIRAD, AFZ and FAO. https://www.feedipedia.org/node/556 Last updated on September 7, 2017, 14:29. ;
